items.name: Kkasi-v1.0
items.description:
Somewhat trained on Kkasi's work: https://twitter.com/kkasi00, though a bit different.

Kkasi is a giantess artist, so this will sometimes be biased towards "from below" angles, and certain poses, and also may generate tiny people and background buildings. Negative prompting it out works if that's not your thing.

I use this more often in combination with other Lora models, so I tend to use it 0.5, but 0.7 works fine by itself.

The examples I provide use my own mixed model: https://civitai.com/models/61700/anythingorange03mix

The "Before" images do not use the LoRA model, and are to differentiate the LoRA from my style of model and prompting. The similar image after is what happens when you put it through img2img with the same prompt, just with the LoRA added (and around 0.5-0.7 denoising). The difference is subtle sometimes, but I personally think it adds just the right amount of spiciness to the image.

items.name: bimbostyleThreeUSD (SD_v1.5) - LORA
items.description:
This is model uses the exact same input as bimbostyleThree and bimbostyleThreeU but was trained on SD_v1.5.ckpt which hopefully means that it's better applicable to other .ckpt in comparison to the normal "Three"

Since i mainly use "draw style" ckpt i can't really say anything about the full potential of this Lora on other ckpt.

Combining this Lora together with bimbostyles (revAnimated) in a "draw style" ckpt give interesting results show in the preview for example in pic 3 with lyriel and i can only recommend trying it out. (i don't know if the same applies to "real" ones as well)

If you mix my models, i would recommend to always put the stronger weighted Lora in the front. i.e.

<lora:bimbostyleThree:0.5>:<lora:bimbostyleTwo:0.3>

And, at least for me, going over a total strength of 1 would result in heavy artefacts (sweetspot round .75-.85)

items.name: Properkissing
items.description:
So I've found SD is excellent for 'solo' / 'pinup' / 'softcore' / 'portrait' / 'sfw non-interactive' type shots out of the box, and pretty darned good for 'hardcore' / 'nsfw' / 'smut' also depending on what model you use, how you prompt, whether you use ControlNet, and whether you're an noob / idiot like me, or a seasoned pro. It also helps if you don't mind going through a ton of stray appendages, misshapen body parts, and 'nightmare fuel' glitches aplenty before you get it right on the 50th tweak to your settings :P

What SD is not so good at ? Kisses. The simple romantic gesture / interraction which involves the intersection of two human photgraphic subjects, overlapping facedata, and a mass of confusion for the algos no doubt, no matter what model, sampler and combination of settings you use.

So much like 'Legshow', here's a Lora / Dreambooth to try to solve this perceived problem.

Trained on a small set of 42 photos for v1. We've got a mixture of 100% sfw and some nsfw in the training data (so I've found bare boobies and/or chests creep in depending on strength and prompts), we've got boy-girl and girl-girl (although it seems to work for boy-boy too as you'll see in one of the sample images I generated once trained) and I've even included a small 'easter egg' with a completely NSFW variation (haven't tested that but the rest works so I'm sure it will too) for a few training shots too.

The 'magic woid' is "properkissing". "French" may work as a modifier, so may "with tongues out". Strengths are really random from what I can tell, based on a combination of model, subjects, other embedding or LORAs, the will of the gods ... who knows :-D

Let me know how you go, and please DO share your outputs as I love to see 'em !

items.description:
Introduction

A LoRA model trained with comic images created by Poper. The trigger tag is 'poper'. The 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) are recommended. 0.6 ~ 0.8 weights are good. The preview images are generated using 1.6 version (original) YesMix.

Cautions (Must Read)

For anime model,

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

  • Some preview images are generated using 'Hires Fix' and upscaled using 'SD Upscale'. Thus, if you wanna generate the preview images, pls download the original preview images and analyze them using 'PNG INFO' in webui to get all generating information.

BTW, make sure set this option in 'Stable Diffusion' settings to 'CPU' to successfully regenerate the preview images with the same seed.

  • The maximum of generating resolution should not exceed 1024 theoretically, otherwise extra/deformed head/limbs will be waiting for you :). Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

items.name: Ilyana (Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance) LoRA
items.description:
Ilyana from Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance, trained on animefull.

Around 0.8 weight works well. Trigger word is 'ilyana fe'. Highly suggest adding 'green shirt', 'purple skirt', 'cape', and 'ribbon' as well for her default outfit.

I'm just gonna say it, this is probably my worst LoRA to date. With a low pool of (honestly not great quality) fanart to work with, I didn't have high hopes that this one would turn out well. And... it kind of didn't, which is really sad because Ilyana is one of my favorite Tellius characters. Still, it's workable and so I'm still going to post it, but understand that it's kind of a pain to use. At least in my experience, it's really finicky with generating good hands and the ribbons she wears on her wrists consistently. Also, it's good with mimicking her blank/tired expression, but also gives her two sets of eyebrows kinda frequently? Weird. Pretty bummed that it's not better, but what can you do I guess.

feeding instructions: she needs one feast every four hours or she will die

items.name: Euan Uglow Style
items.description:
Euan Uglow a British painter known for his meticulous and precise approach to figurative art. His work is often associated with the school of realism, though his style goes beyond mere representation and delves into the realm of abstraction and formalism.

Uglow's paintings are characterized by their careful attention to detail, precise measurements, and a focus on the human figure. He was known for using a methodical approach to his work, spending extensive time on each painting, meticulously building up layers of paint and capturing the subtle nuances of light and form.

His subjects ranged from still lifes and interiors to portraits and nudes. Uglow had a keen interest in capturing the play of light on objects and the human body, often using controlled lighting setups to enhance the three-dimensional quality of his subjects.

Uglow's approach to composition was highly considered, with a focus on geometric precision and formal balance. He often employed grids, measured intervals, and careful observation to achieve a sense of order and structure within his paintings.

Despite the technical precision of his work, Uglow's paintings also carried a sense of quiet contemplation and intimacy. His subjects often appeared absorbed in their own thoughts or engaged in mundane activities, creating a sense of stillness and introspection in his art.

Throughout his career, Euan Uglow received recognition for his exceptional skill and dedication to his craft. His work has been exhibited internationally, and he has influenced subsequent generations of artists with his unique blend of meticulous realism and formal abstraction.

Euan Uglow's paintings continue to captivate viewers with their meticulous detail, thoughtful composition, and a profound exploration of light and form. His dedication to precision and his ability to evoke a sense of quiet beauty in his subjects have solidified his place as a significant figure in the realm of figurative art.

Read: The Lora/parrot is planned to create spaces, also the function of creating graffiti is incorporated.
If you want to use it to interact with characters, then they will tend to look like graffiti, if you set that option. Otherwise they will not appear.
I repeat, it is not a Lora for the characters to interact, rather it is a Lora dedicated to creating the place itself and the effort is put into that. If you want to achieve interactions you're going to have to put Lora on ezforce.

items.name: StellarMix
items.description:
A mixture of my favourite checkpoints.

This model merge was made during my spare time for fun, as I was curious about mixing completely different checkpoints together. I'm currently unsure if I will improve this checkpoint but I wanted to share because why not.

It's not great at extremely detailed backgrounds but I like its outcomes.

I'm fairly new to all this, so I apologise if I cannot answer questions.

Simple Prompts

Most of the images I've generated with this checkpoint are fairly straightforward to a certain extent. I haven't really tested very descriptive prompts but I would love to see if it's possible.

NSFW Content

This checkpoint is capable of doing NSFW content, although I haven't thoroughly tested it so I do not know the limitations.

VAE

No VAE was baked into this model, so you have the freedom to pick and play your sort of style. I was using Pastel Waifu Diffusion for most of my images. I have tested it with kl-f8-anime2 and that works too.

Issues

There does seem to be an issue with hair colours. For some reason, solid colours like black often generate blue highlights. Iâ€™m unsure what causes this, so if someone knows how it can be improved I would greatly appreciate it. Thanks!

Post your image generations!

It would be great to see what sort of generations could be created from this checkpoint.

Recommended Generation

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Steps: 25+

  • CFG: 5-7 (Not really played around - Usually did 7).

  • Clip Skip: 2

  • Hires.Fix: R-ESRGAN 4X+ Anime6B

    • Hires Steps: 12-30

    • Denoising Strength: 0.4+

    • Upscale: 2

I also like to use 4x-UltraSharp on my images sometimes but that's definitely not required.

Have fun generating those images! I look forward to seeing what gets created.

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

items.name: FMD Muramasa
items.description:
EDIT: Added 1e4-05 in case you experience smeared/ruined eyes or some other overbake issue, added a few different comparison graphs to that version's preview (open in new window to view at full resolution). I think it doesn't follow the style so strongly so dunno if it's an improvement.

Can be used as style model just fine, but also encompasses a fuckton of characters.
First grid is misleading, it didn't actually have a chara lora loaded. The rest of Sumika ones are tested against her chara LoRA properly.

I've squeezed every FMD Muramasa character in here. Around 20 characters. Almost all of them with shit datasets. Don't expect miracles. Well, it works, how good it is might depend on the character itself.

Regarding versions I believe 1e4-10 is best, 5e4-10 is mostly the same but I think it's failed with the style(?), seems noticeable on the color pallette with Sumika. As for 7e5 I think it does the minor characters best, if you wanna try reproducing them. 14400 for archival purposes, might be useful for someone I guess.

Anyways, since individual character LoRAs lost some artstyle in exchange for actually working and getting details right, this one exists to give them the official style back. Just use it alongside them - this one should probably have lower weight than the character one to not mess details up but you'll have to experiment.

As for prompting for all the characters in here it's going to be part of their name in most cases. Your best bet is checking the tags via additional networks extension or trying either name or surname and seeing which works.

Exceptions are "Muramasa Nisei" "Grandfather" and "Minato Subaru". Let me know if you want any of these characters separated into a proper LoRA. Though alot of them don't have enough images for proper datasets so might end up like Doushin or Kageaki.

items.name: Laura Matsuda [Street Fighter V]
items.description:
My first attempt to do a female character. I thought it would be easier, but Laura has too many clothes parts and features. Also, I tried to do more than one outfit, and I think it was too much. YET... the model works well with anime style. Not a fan of very realistic results. I try to emphasize (anime style) and sometimes put (realistic) as negative prompt. Let me know your opinion.
Trigger word is LauraMatsuda

Hair usually shows up, but if you need, include: sidecut, cornrows, and/or cornrows braids.

Other trigger words: green minishirt, denim minishorts, black thong, sandals, bracelets, bracelets2, choker, green tanktop, martial arts pants, black belt, green pants, shin guards (doesn't work well).
